    • Field Detail

      • routeName

        public java.lang.String routeName
        The name of the parentRoute. Note: This cannot contain whitespace characters (ie spaces, tabs, or new lines), as its used in a url.

      • color

        public int color
        The color of the parentRoute. This is optional, as there is a high chance that the parentRoute does not have one.

        This is an int instead of a Color object because for whatever reason android stores its colors as ints.

      • stops

        public Stop[] stops
        The array of stops for this parentRoute. This may be empty / null if the parentRoute has not been initialized, and the stops haven't been loaded.

      • buses

        public Bus[] buses
        The array of buses that belong to this route.

      • asyncBusUpdater

        public UpdateBuses asyncBusUpdater
        The asynchronous method that updates the buses for this route.

      • polyLineCoordinates

        public com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng[] polyLineCoordinates
        The array of LatLng coordinates that will be used to create the polyline (if enabled). This should be initialized with an array of length 0.

      • updateThread

        public UpdateThread updateThread
        The network thread that updates this given route.

        Parameters:
        routeName - The name of the parentRoute. e sure this does NOT contain any whitespace characters!
        color - The parentRoute's color. This is optional, and of the color is non-existent simply use the Route(String routeName) constructor.

    • Method Detail

      • generateRoutes

        public static Route[] generateRoutes(org.json.JSONObject masterSchedule)
        Dynamically generates the childRoutes that are used by parsing the master schedule. This may return an empty parentRoute array if there was an issue parsing the data, or if there were no childRoutes to parse based off the master schedule.
        Parameters:
        masterSchedule - The master schedule JSONObject from the RouteMatch server.
        Returns:
        An array of childRoutes that can be tracked.

      • enableRoutes

        public static Route[] enableRoutes(java.lang.String routeName,
                                   Route[] oldRoutes)
        Enabled a parentRoute by parentRoute name, and returns a new array of enabled childRoutes including the previously enabled childRoutes.
        Parameters:
        routeName - The new parentRoute to enable (by parentRoute name).
        oldRoutes - The array of old childRoutes that were previously enabled. If there were no previously enabled childRoutes then this must be an array of size 0.
        Returns:
        The array of childRoutes that are now being tracked.

      • disableRoute

        public static Route[] disableRoute(java.lang.String routeName,
                                   Route[] oldRoutes)
        Disables a parentRoute by name, and removes all elements of that parentRoute from the map (except stops).
        Parameters:
        routeName - The parentRoute the be disabled by name.
        oldRoutes - The array of old, though currently enabled childRoutes.
        Returns:
        The array of childRoutes still to be tracked, with the omission of the parentRoute that was to be removed. If there are no more childRoutes that are to be enabled, then an array of size 0 will be returned.

      • loadStops

        public Stop[] loadStops(RouteMatch routeMatch)
        Loads the stops from the provided url. If there was an error parsing the JSON data for the stop object, then this will return what stops it had parsed successfully up until that point. As a result, the Stop array returned may be smaller than expected, or have a length of 0.
        Parameters:
        routeMatch - The parentRoute match instance (for pulling from the RouteMatch server).
        Returns:
        The array of stops that were loaded.

      • loadPolyLineCoordinates

        public com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng[] loadPolyLineCoordinates(RouteMatch routeMatch)

        Parameters:
        routeMatch - The RouteMatch object.
        Returns:
        The initialized array of LatLng coordinates.
